22
00:00:44,405 --> 00:00:45,540
All right,

23
00:00:45,624 --> 00:00:46,628
what's the problem here?

24
00:00:46,712 --> 00:00:48,153
I don't know what's real.

25
00:00:48,238 --> 00:00:50,249
That's a fun thing to think
about on the way to school.

26
00:00:50,333 --> 00:00:51,599
Get up and get dressed.

27
00:00:51,684 --> 00:00:53,069
Maybe I'm already dressed.

28
00:00:53,153 --> 00:00:55,981
Maybe I'm wearing
a zoot suit and spats.

29
00:00:56,324 --> 00:00:58,778
That's a shoe covering that's
short for "spatterdasher."

30
00:00:58,907 --> 00:00:59,998
Or is it?

31
00:01:00,083 --> 00:01:01,425
There's no way to know.

32
00:01:01,509 --> 00:01:03,296
Here's what I know: I don't have
time for this nonsense.

33
00:01:03,380 --> 00:01:04,689
What is time?

34
00:01:04,773 --> 00:01:05,919
What is sense?

35
00:01:06,004 --> 00:01:07,481
What is "is"?

36
00:01:07,566 --> 00:01:08,825
Sheldon, I mean it.

37
00:01:08,910 --> 00:01:11,220
I remember
when things meant things.

38
00:01:11,519 --> 00:01:13,437
All right, I'm gonna count
to three. One...

39
00:01:13,521 --> 00:01:16,044
Believing in numbers...
That takes me back.

40
00:01:16,157 --> 00:01:18,099
- Two...
- To be or not to be.

41
00:01:18,184 --> 00:01:19,703
Shakespeare was onto something.

42
00:01:19,788 --> 00:01:21,536
It's your last chance.

43
00:01:22,012 --> 00:01:23,534
Have you ever wondered
if you're the tongue

44
00:01:23,618 --> 00:01:25,902
of a multidimensional being
trying to taste something

45
00:01:25,987 --> 00:01:27,856
you can never even understand?

46
00:01:28,494 --> 00:01:30,017
I have.

47
00:01:34,290 --> 00:01:35,840
I talked to him.

48
00:01:36,840 --> 00:01:38,244
Where is your mother?

49
00:01:38,328 --> 00:01:39,676
She had to leave for work.

50
00:01:39,833 --> 00:01:41,030
I have to work, too.

51
00:01:41,114 --> 00:01:43,119
You also get to take me
to school.

52
00:01:43,203 --> 00:01:44,860
What am I supposed to do
about your brother?

53
00:01:44,944 --> 00:01:46,122
Call me old-fashioned,

54
00:01:46,206 --> 00:01:47,558
but I say spank him.

55
00:01:47,986 --> 00:01:49,509
Your mom won't let me.

56
00:01:50,426 --> 00:01:53,341
<i>♪ Nobody else
is stronger than I am ♪</i>

57
